           Storage Account
<------------------------------------------------------->
A Storage Account in cloud computing (especially in Azure) is a service that provides a secure, scalable, and highly available way to store data in the cloud.
Key Features of a Storage Account
âœ… Scalability â€“ Can handle massive amounts of data efficiently.
âœ… Security â€“ Supports encryption, role-based access control (RBAC), and private endpoints.
âœ… Durability â€“ Provides replication options like LRS, GRS, ZRS, and RA-GRS to prevent data loss.
âœ… Cost-Effective â€“ Different pricing tiers based on usage and redundancy requirements.
âœ… Multi-Protocol Support â€“ Works with REST APIs, SDKs, CLI, and PowerShell.
